175  /-!
176  ### Converting between expressions and numerals
177  
178  There are a number of ways to convert between expressions and numerals, depending on the input and
179  output types and whether you want to infer the necessary type classes.
180  
181  See also the tactics `expr.of_nat`, `expr.of_int`, `expr.of_rat`.
182  -/
183  
184  
185  /--
186  `nat.mk_numeral n` embeds `n` as a numeral expression inside a type with 0, 1, and +.
187  `type`: an expression representing the target type. This must live in Type 0.
188  `has_zero`, `has_one`, `has_add`: expressions of the type `has_zero %%type`, etc.
189   -/
190  meta def nat.mk_numeral (type has_zero has_one has_add : expr) : ℕ → expr :=
id                                                            └──┘    ┴ ┴ └──┘
src                                                           └──┘    ┴   └──┘
typ                                                           └──┘    ┴ ┴ └──┘
doc                                                           └──┘        └──┘

371  library_note "open expressions"
372  "Some declarations work with open expressions, i.e. an expr that has free variables.
373  Terms will free variables are not well-typed, and one should not use them in tactics like
374  `infer_type` or `unify`. You can still do syntactic analysis/manipulation on them.
375  The reason for working with open types is for performance: instantiating variables requires
376  iterating through the expression. In one performance test `pi_binders` was more than 6x
377  quicker than `mk_local_pis` (when applied to the type of all imported declarations 100x)."
378

526  /-!
527  ### `is_eta_expansion`
528  
529   In this section we define the tactic `is_eta_expansion` which checks whether an expression
530    is an eta-expansion of a structure. (not to be confused with eta-expanion for `λ`).
531  
532  -/
533  
534  namespace expr
535  
536  open tactic
537  
538  /-- `is_eta_expansion_of args univs l` checks whether for all elements `(nm, pr)` in `l` we have
539    `pr = nm.{univs} args`.
540    Used in `is_eta_expansion`, where `l` consists of the projections and the fields of the value we
541    want to eta-reduce. -/
542  meta def is_eta_expansion_of (args : list expr) (univs : list level) (l : list (name × expr)) :
id                                        └──┘ └──┘           └──┘ └───┘       └──┘  └──┘ ┴ └──┘
src                                       └──┘ └──┘           └──┘ └───┘       └──┘  └──┘ ┴ └──┘
typ                                       └──┘ └──┘           └──┘ └───┘       └──┘  └──┘ ┴ └──┘
doc                                            └──┘                └───┘             └──┘   └──┘
543    bool :=
id     └──┘
src    └──┘
typ    └──┘
544  l.all $ λ⟨proj, val⟩, val = (const proj univs).mk_app args
id   ┴└──┘    ┴└──┘  └─┘       ┴  └───┘      └───┘ └────┘  └──┘
src   └──┘                     ┴  └───┘            └────┘
typ  ┴└──┘    ┴└──┘  └─┘       ┴  └───┘      └───┘ └────┘  └──┘
545  
546  /-- `is_eta_expansion_test l` checks whether there is a list of expresions `args` such that for all
547    elements `(nm, pr)` in `l` we have `pr = nm args`. If so, returns the last element of `args`.
548    Used in `is_eta_expansion`, where `l` consists of the projections and the fields of the value we
549    want to eta-reduce. -/
550  meta def is_eta_expansion_test : list (name × expr) → option expr
id                                    └──┘  └──┘ ┴ └──┘  ┴ └────┘ └──┘
src                                   └──┘  └──┘ ┴ └──┘    └────┘ └──┘
typ                                   └──┘  └──┘ ┴ └──┘  ┴ └────┘ └──┘
doc                                         └──┘   └──┘           └──┘
551  | []              := none
id     └┘                 └──┘
src    └┘                 └──┘
typ    └┘                 └──┘
552  | (⟨proj, val⟩::l) :=
id       └──┘  └─┘ └┘┴
src                └┘
typ      └──┘  └─┘ └┘┴
553    match val.get_app_fn with
id              └─────────┘
src             └─────────┘
typ             └─────────┘
554    | (const nm univs : expr) :=
id        └───┘ └┘ └───┘   └──┘
src       └───┘            └──┘
typ       └───┘ └┘ └───┘   └──┘
doc                        └──┘
555      if nm = proj then
id             ┴
src            ┴
typ            ┴
556        let args := val.get_app_args in
id             └──┘       └───────────┘
src                       └───────────┘
typ            └──┘       └───────────┘
557        let e := args.ilast in

src                     └────┘

src           └─────────────────┘                   └──┘        └──┘
typ           └─────────────────┘ └──┘              └──┘ ┴      └──┘
doc           └─────────────────┘
559      else
560        none
id         └──┘
src        └──┘
typ        └──┘
561    | _                       := none
id                                  └──┘
src                                 └──┘
typ                                 └──┘
562    end
563  
564  /-- `is_eta_expansion_aux val l` checks whether `val` can be eta-reduced to an expression `e`.
565    Here `l` is intended to consists of the projections and the fields of `val`.
566    This tactic calls `is_eta_expansion_test l`, but first removes all proofs from the list `l` and
567    afterward checks whether the retulting expression `e` unifies with `val`.
568    This last check is necessary, because `val` and `e` might have different types. -/
569  meta def is_eta_expansion_aux (val : expr) (l : list (name × expr)) : tactic (option expr) :=
id                                        └──┘       └──┘  └──┘ ┴ └──┘     └────┘  └────┘ └──┘
src                                       └──┘       └──┘  └──┘ ┴ └──┘     └────┘  └────┘ └──┘
typ                                       └──┘       └──┘  └──┘ ┴ └──┘     └────┘  └────┘ └──┘
doc                                       └──┘             └──┘   └──┘                    └──┘
570  do l' ← l.mfilter (λ⟨proj, val⟩, bnot <$> is_proof val),
id      └┘   ┴└──────┘   ┴      └─┘   └──┘ └─┘ └──────┘
src           └──────┘                └──┘ └─┘ └──────┘
typ     └┘   ┴└──────┘   ┴      └─┘   └──┘ └─┘ └──────┘
571    match is_eta_expansion_test l' with
id           └───────────────────┘ └┘
src          └───────────────────┘
typ          └───────────────────┘ └┘
doc          └───────────────────┘
572    | some e := option.map (λ _, e) <$> try_core (unify e val)
id       └──┘ ┴    └────────┘    ┴     └─┘ └──────┘  └───┘   └─┘
src      └──┘      └────────┘          └─┘ └──────┘  └───┘
typ      └──┘ ┴    └────────┘    ┴     └─┘ └──────┘  └───┘   └─┘
doc                                                  └───┘
573    | none   := return none
id       └──┘      └────┘ └──┘
src      └──┘      └────┘ └──┘
typ      └──┘      └────┘ └──┘
574    end
575  
576  /-- `is_eta_expansion val` checks whether there is an expression `e` such that `val` is the
577    eta-expansion of `e`.
578    With eta-expansion we here mean the eta-expansion of a structure, not of a function.
579    For example, the eta-expansion of `x : α × β` is `⟨x.1, x.2⟩`.
580    This assumes that `val` is a fully-applied application of the constructor of a structure.
581  
582    This is useful to reduce expressions generated by the notation
583      `{ field_1 := _, ..other_structure }`
584    If `other_structure` is itself a field of the structure, then the elaborator will insert an
585    eta-expanded version of `other_structure`. -/
586  meta def is_eta_expansion (val : expr) : tactic (option expr) := do
id                                    └──┘    └────┘  └────┘ └──┘
src                                   └──┘    └────┘  └────┘ └──┘
typ                                   └──┘    └────┘  └────┘ └──┘
doc                                   └──┘                   └──┘
587    e ← get_env,
id     ┴   └─────┘
src        └─────┘
typ    ┴   └─────┘
588    type ← infer_type val,
id     └──┘   └────────┘ └─┘
src           └────────┘
typ    └──┘   └────────┘ └─┘
doc           └────────┘
589    projs ← e.structure_fields_full type.get_app_fn.const_name,
id     └───┘   ┴└────────────────────┘ └──┘└─────────┘└─────────┘
src             └────────────────────┘     └─────────┘└─────────┘
typ    └───┘   ┴└────────────────────┘ └──┘└─────────┘└─────────┘
doc             └────────────────────┘
590    let args := (val.get_app_args).drop type.get_app_args.length,
id         └──┘     └─┘└───────────┘ └──┘  └──┘└───────────┘└─────┘
src                    └───────────┘ └──┘      └───────────┘└─────┘
typ        └──┘     └─┘└───────────┘ └──┘  └──┘└───────────┘└─────┘
591    is_eta_expansion_aux val (projs.zip args)
id     └──────────────────┘ └─┘  └───┘└──┘ └──┘
src    └──────────────────┘           └──┘
typ    └──────────────────┘ └─┘  └───┘└──┘ └──┘
doc    └──────────────────┘
592  
593  end expr
